      "span_text": "Compared to intermittent infusion of 2 g cefepime every 12 hours, continuous infusion of 4 g/day cefepime over 24 hours could significantly reduce the treatment duration in adult neurosurgical patients with postoperative intracranial infections (6.6±1.9 days vs 7.8±2.6 days; P=0.036), and achieve higher %T>MIC for cefepime concentrations in cerebrospinal fluid (for MICs of 4 µg/mL, 83.3% vs 25%; for MICs of 8 µg/mL, 75% vs 0%)."
